  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "An account is a named record that tracks increases and decreases in a specific asset, liability, equity, revenue, or expense. It's the basic classification unit of [double-entry bookkeeping](./double-entry-bookkeeping.md) — every transaction is recorded by [debiting](./debit-and-credit.md) one or more accounts and [crediting](./debit-and-credit.md) one or more others.",
